\begin_layout Standard
We have demonstrated an effective algorithm for removing ringing artifacts
 from coded images and videos.
 The proposed CDEF algorithm is based on the conditional replacement filter
 (CRF) and a constrained low-pass filter (CLPF) and takes into account the
 direction of the patterns it is filtering to reduce the risk of blurring.
 Objective results show a bit-rate reduction up to 7.7% on video sequences.
 
